# Do NOT run paid LLM commands without explicit approval

This project's pipeline calls a hosted LLM (Together AI via `LLM_PROVIDER=openai`
in `.env`). Each batch run can cost real money. Stop and confirm with the user
before kicking off ANY of the following, even "just to test":

- `python main.py` (full batch)
- `python main.py batch ...`
- `python main.py stage <name>` for any stage other than `topic-clustering`
  (the only stage that does no LLM calls)
- `python main.py process ...`
- Any `docker compose exec pipeline python main.py ...` variant
- Any `curl` or HTTP request to `/match-post-topics`, `/topic-response/...`,
  or `/process` on the running API container

Read-only smoke checks that do NOT call the LLM are fine without asking:

- `python -c "import main; ..."` import checks
- SQLite reads against `data/pipeline.db`
- `curl http://localhost:8000/health`, `/topics`, `/topics/{id}` (these are DB reads)
- `docker compose build`, `docker compose ps`, `docker compose logs`

If a task seems to require running the pipeline (e.g. "verify the changes
end-to-end"), describe the run you would do and ask first. Do not background
it, do not run it "briefly to see if it works."

The cost-per-batch on the current fixture (`test_data/mastodon_real.json`,
~1500 posts) is on the order of single-digit cents per full run, but small
costs accumulate and the user wants to be the one who decides when to spend.
